Html:
I know it's an old question, but it turns up pretty high on Google and I have an ok solution.<br />
<br />
You can inherit DataGrid and define the columns in xaml. Then you use the inherited type instead of DataGrid.<br />
<br />
My specific example was<br />
<pre><code>&lt;DataGrid x:Class=&quot;...Controls.ImportDataGrid&quot;  
           xmlns=&quot;...&gt;
    &lt;DataGrid.Columns&gt;
        &lt;DataGridTemplateColumn.../&gt;
        ...
    &lt;/DataGrid.Columns&gt;
&lt;/DataGrid&gt;
</code></pre>

and then using ImportDataGrid where I would use the DataGrid.<br />
